ackground light connect smoothly, within systematic errors, with\nthe mean spectrum in 2009-2011 observed at lower energies by the Fermi-LAT. The\nabsorption-corrected MAGIC spectrum is flat with no apparent turn down up to\n400 GeV. The multiwavelength light curve shows increasing flux in radio and\noptical bands that could point to a common origin from the same region of the\njet. The large separation between the two peaks of the constructed\nnon-simultaneous spectral energy distribution also requires an extremely high\nDoppler factor if an one zone synchrotron self-Compton model is applied. We\nfind that a two-component synchrotron self-Compton model describes the spectral\nenergy distribution of the source well, if the source is located at z~0.6.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 2 Jan 2014 16:17:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 11 Jun 2014 09:20:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-09-05"}
